🛠️ Getting Started
Follow these steps to get TaskFlow Elite running on your local machine.

1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd taskflow-elite
```

2. Set Up the Core Library
   Navigate to the core directory:

```bash
cd core
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

Build the library:

```bash
npm run build
```

Return to the root directory:

```bash
cd ..
```

3. Set Up the UI
   Navigate to the UI directory:

```bash
cd ui
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

Start the development server:

```bash
npm run dev
```

4. Access the App
   Open your browser and visit:
   http://localhost:5173
   ✨ Features
   ✅ Task Management
   • Full CRUD operations: create, read, update, and delete tasks.
   • Filter tasks by priority, tags, status, or search terms.
   • Reorder tasks using intuitive drag-and-drop functionality.
   📊 Analytics
   • Visualize task completion rates with an interactive chart.
   🌗 Enhanced User Experience
   • Toggle between light and dark modes.
   • Receive browser notifications for overdue tasks and reminders.
   • Earn points and badges for completing tasks (gamification).
   📤 Data Export
   • Export your tasks to a CSV file for easy sharing or backup.
   🏗️ Architecture Overview
   🔧 Core Logic
   • Located in the `core` directory.
   • Implemented as a reusable TypeScript library.
   • Handles task operations via TaskManager and includes analytics utilities.
   🖼️ User Interface
   • Built with Vue 3 in the `ui` directory.
   • Uses Vite for lightning-fast development and builds.
   🧠 State Management
   • Powered by Pinia to manage tasks and user stats.
   🌐 Routing
   • Managed using Vue Router.
